{"lemma":"رِفْقَةٍ","slug":"رِفْقَةٍ","root":"ر.ف.ق","root_slug":"ر-ف-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ف-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16202","n16203","n16204","n16205"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%81%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"company (which one has when one is accompanied)","examples":[{"text":"أعلنت وسائل إعلام فرنسية، أن باريس تسلمت ثلاثة أطفال لزوجين فرنسيين سافروا للقتال في العراق، بينما والدتهم لا تزال محتجزة من قبل السلطات المحلية العراقية برفقة طفل رابع صغير.","english":"French media has reported that Paris has received three children belonging to a French couple that has travelled to fight in Iraq, whilst their mother continues to be under arrest of local Iraqi authorities, in the company of a fourth small child."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/rif.qa/","/ruf.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16202","headword_ar":"رَفْقَةٌ","root":"rfq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16203","headword_ar":"رُفْقَةٌ","root":"rfq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, O, Mgh, Msb, K,) in the dial. of Temeem, (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifoqapN","text_ar":"رِفْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) in the dial. of Keys, (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafoqapN","text_ar":"رَفْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and on the authority of Ibn-Tal-hah ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rufaAqapN","text_ar":"رُفَاقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [in which this last is said to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vumaAmapu","text_ar":"ثُمَامَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to indicate that it is with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":", but not (as will be shown below, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiyqN","text_ar":"رَفِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) that it is without tenween, imperfectly decl., and determinate like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ufoqapu","text_ar":"الرُّفْقَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persons travelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeying, together;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company of persons"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with whom one is travelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeying; but not when they have separated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons with whom one travels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeys, as long as they are congregated in one place of assembly, and in one journey; but not when they have separated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifaAqN","text_ar":"رِفَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Mgh, Msb, K,) which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rufoqapN","text_ar":"رُفْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rufaqN","text_ar":"رُفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rufoqapN","text_ar":"رُفْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arofaAqN","text_ar":"اَرْفَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifoqapN","text_ar":"رِفْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifaqN","text_ar":"رِفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rufoqapN","text_ar":"رُفْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a quasi-pl. n. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiyqN","text_ar":"رَفِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or syn. with this last used in a pl. sense; and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifaqN","text_ar":"رِفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rufaqN","text_ar":"رُفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [quasi-pl. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqN","text_ar":"رَفَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) [Golius explains the first and second and third, as on the authority of the KL, by the words “ consortium, societas: ” but in my copy of the KL, I find only the first and second; and these are explained only by the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Grwh hmrAhAn","text_ar":"گروه همراهان"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with the renderings which I have given above.] ―         -b2-  The pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifaAqN","text_ar":"رِفَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Camels upon which people have gone forth to purvey for themselves wheat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other provisions from the towns"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages; each,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every, company being termed a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rufoqap","text_ar":"رُفْقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTaAnapN","text_ar":"رَطَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","O","Mgh","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n16204","headword_ar":"رِفْقَةٌ","root":"rfq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16205","headword_ar":"رَفِقَةٌ","root":"rfq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to a she-camel: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arofaqu","text_ar":"اَرْفَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}